title: Massey teams both place 11th
text:
Brandon Sun - PRINT EDITION Massey teams both place 11th 
Vincent Massey finished 11th place in both varsity boys’ and varsity girls’ AAAA team competitions at the provincial high school cross-country championships at Epinette Creek Trail in Spruce Woods Provincial Park on Wednesday. 
The team champions were determined by the placings of each school’s five fastest runners. The boys ran 5,000 metres, while the girls ran 3,000. 
Somerset’s Prairie Mountain school placed third in the A/AAA junior varsity girls’ competition and sixth in the A/AAA varsity girls’ race. Ste. Rose du Lac placed seventh among A/AAA varsity girls, while Treherne was 10th. 
Treherne was fifth in the A/AAA JV boys’ category, with Glenboro ninth. Ste. Rose was fifth among A/AAA varsity boys’ teams, while Baldur was sixth.
